Explanation:

- The route is defined in routes/admin.php as a resource route for comments routed to App\Http\Controllers\Admin\CommentController. The update action maps to PUT /admin/comments/{comment}.
- The controller's update method accepts a CommentsRequest and a Comment model (route model binding). So the path has a required path parameter named "comment" which represents the comment identifier used for route model binding — this is an integer id.
- The CommentsRequest class defines the validation rules for the update payload. The rules() method requires:
  - content: required (string)
  - posted_at: required and must be a date after_or_equal to the comment's post posted_at — prepareForValidation parses posted_at with Carbon, and the Comment model casts posted_at to datetime. In the OpenAPI/Swagger parameter schema we use type "string" with format "date-time" and add a short description about the after_or_equal constraint.
  - author_id: required and must exist in users.id (integer)
- The update accepts a request body containing these fields. In Swagger 2.0 this should be represented as a single body parameter with a JSON object schema that has properties content, posted_at, and author_id, with all three listed as required.
- No $ref are used.

